div.p: SIENNESE, a duchy in Italy ; bounded on the north by the Florentino, on the ſouth by the Mediterranean sea and the duchy of Castro, on the east by the Perugino and Orvietano, and on the west by the Florentino and the Tuſcan ſea ; being about 55 miles in length, and as much in breadth. The soil is pretty fertile, eſpecially in mulberry trees, which feed a great number of silk-worms ; and there are ſeveral mineral ſprings. Sienna is the capital town.
